        <detaileddescription>
<para>stores a mapping from keys K to values V in one of two forms: 1) as dense map (vector) preferable when there are few missing keys in a range [0, endKey) 2) as hash map preferable when valid keys are a small subset of the range Generated from class <computeroutput>MR::MapOrHashMap&lt;MR::UndirectedEdgeId, MR::EdgeId&gt;</computeroutput>. Supported <computeroutput><ref refid="common_8h_1ac983b89bddb9b22c9b416f31399f0095" kindref="member">MR_PassBy</ref></computeroutput> modes: <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_DefaultConstruct</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_Copy</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_Move</computeroutput> (and <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_DefaultArgument</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_NoObject</computeroutput> if supported by the callee). </para>
