        <detaileddescription>
<para>given input bit-set (src), converts each id corresponding to set bit using given map, and sets its bit in the resulting bit set Generated from function <computeroutput>MR::mapEdges</computeroutput>. Parameter <computeroutput>map</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>src</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Never returns null. Returns an instance allocated on the heap! Must call <computeroutput><ref refid="MRBitSet_8h_1a5f5b1d2e5d4d71fe8be1eddbe649ca16" kindref="member">MR_UndirectedEdgeBitSet_Destroy()</ref></computeroutput> to free it when you&apos;re done using it. </para>
